.css-1noe2rc *{color:#505863;line-height:1.4em;}.css-1noe2rc .ecgq1xb1{padding-left:0;}.css-1noe2rc .ecgq1xb1 .ecgq1xb0{margin:0 0 8px 0;}.css-1noe2rc ol,.css-1noe2rc ul{padding-left:32px;}.css-1noe2rc li{margin:10px;margin-bottom:5px;margin-left:20px;line-height:1.4em;}.css-58vpdc{margin-bottom:24px;}.css-58vpdc ul{margin:5px 0 10px 20px;}.css-58vpdc ul > br{display:none;}.css-58vpdc ul > li{margin-left:0;}.css-58vpdc li{padding:0;}We are building a new collections analytics team in our risk department to help develop smart, customer focused strategies and solutions for our customers. Our team might be small, but we have the opportunity to make a big impact and support our business growth strategy across all our markets (currently Poland, Spain, Russia & India)!

A day in this job

In the collections analytics team you will be searching for data driven opportunities to develop customer focused strategies for those customers who have missed payments that also balances risk and operational cost. You will work very closely with other teams and stakeholders across collections operations and the wider business whilst looking for sustainable strategies that drive value across all our markets.

In this role you will help create transparency around our collections processes and subsequent impact on financial performance by designing, creating and maintaining the necessary reports. Through your deep understanding of how our customers are reacting to different strategies you will be able to identify strategy improvements that will reduce loss and enhance the profitability of the different portfolios. To achieve this, you will have to build close relationships with different teams and stay up to date with changes in processes, systems or regulation across the relevant countries.

Desired skills & experience

Degree in Mathematics, Economics, Finance or Scientific discipline;
3 years + in analytical/reporting team ideally in risk or collections;
Strong coding (SQL or R) and visualisation skills (e.g. Tableau/Qlikview/Excel);
Keen interest in understanding processes and an eye for detail;
Good communicator - able to build strong working relationships across different teams;
Ability to structure and display information in an intuitive manner;
Fluent in English  any other languages would be a plus;
Some experience in A/B testing is a plus but not essential.

What is in it for you?

Collections analytics is essential in supporting our business growth strategy and you will be in a position where you are able to collaborate with other teams and many stakeholders as well as directly influence the success of the business. Due to the agility of the business, you will be able to quickly see the impact of your proposals on customers and financial results. You will have the opportunity to work with talented people from various different backgrounds and professional experiences.

At Kreditech, we like to constantly challenge the status quo and improve our ways of working. We are a data-driven organization and enthusiastic about agile methodology. Diversity is in our DNA and we strongly believe that having different perspectives, experiences and backgrounds will lead to the best environment for our employees and better products for our customers. If this sounds like the kind of company you'd like to work with, please apply here!
